casebody.data:
Algie, Appellant, v. Larned et al., Respondents. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. March 3, 1890.)

Argued before Larrbmore, C. J., and Daly and Bischoff, JJ.

Larned & Warren, for respondents. Per Curiam.

Motion by respondents to dismiss appeal, taken from the judgment and order denying motion for a new trial, for the failure to prosecute appeal with diligence, and for his failure to make and serve his case on appeal. Granted, with costs, and $10 costs of motion.
